==Latin==
===Suffix===
'''-itas,''' '''[[Wiktionary Appendix:Latin third declension|-itātis]]''' ''f''

# suffix appended usually to adjectives to form a noun indicating a state of being.

====Examples====
*masculinus - masculinitas
*activus - activitas
*civis - civitas
*fidelis - fidelitas

====Translations====
*English: [[-ity]]
*French: [[ité]]
*Italian: [[-ità]]
*Spanish: [[-idad]], [[-edad]], [[-dad]]
